examples.en: The grassy hills were sheathed in mist.
She looked back up the grassy slope.
She was sitting on a grassy bank.
There were grassy tussocks throughout the marsh.
The grassy plain gave way to an extensive swamp.
Grassy plains used to cover large portions of America's midsection.
A Greek revival belvedere stands majestically on a grassy knoll overlooking the river.
